SYNOPSIS
	mixed *get_attribute( void)
	mixed *get_attribute( object obj)
	int    get_attribute( string attr)
	int    get_attribute( string attr, object obj)

DESCRIPTION
	Get the value of a given attribute 'attr' or an array containing all
	attributes, both names and values.
	If no object 'obj' is given, the current object is used.

	If an attribute name is given, then the value of that attribute is
	returned if found. -1 is returned if it is not found

	When the attribute name is not given, an array of the following
	format is returned:	
	({ attr_name0, attr_value0, .., attr_nameN, attr_valueN })

SEE ALSO
	attributes(C), add_attribute(E), add_prot_attribute(E),
	delete_attribute(E), query_attribute(E)
